HEADWORD: Monosyllabism
<hw>Mon`o*syl"la*bism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of
consisting of monosyllables, or having a monosyllabic form; frequent
occurrence of monosyllables.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monosyllable</ent>⟦br⟧
